Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with flow scheduling in networking, which is a core topic in this sub-category. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses game theory to design a distributed virtual game to solve the flow scheduling problem. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed algorithm to solve the flow scheduling problem. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses online learning schemes to generalize the flow scheduling problem to situations of unknown environment. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the optimization of a system (flow scheduling) in an unknown environment, which falls under this sub-category.
